S7. Cytotoxicity Tests with the MTT Assay
MTT assay was done to look for cytotoxic compounds by screening "hits" from initial high-throughput drug
screening for cytotoxic effects. Cytotoxicity was monitored by using 3-(4,5-dimethyl-2-thiazolyl)-2,5-diphenyl-
2H-tetrazolium bromide (MTT). A colorimetric reaction is used in this assay to measure the reducing potential of
